<DOC><DOCNO> AP890608-0238 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-08-89 0817EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks     06-08 0117</FIRST><SECOND>BC-British Stocks,0123</SECOND><HEAD>London Shares Sharply Higher</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Stock prices were sharply higher at midday Thursdayas several favorable factors provoked some healthy buying by Britishinstitutions.   Prompted by a steady pound and a rise on Wall Street,institutions entered the market in force after remaining largely onthe sidelines in previous sessions, dealers said.   Share prices advanced across a broad front, with specialsituations and takeover speculation provoking strong rises inselected blue chip issues.   At midday, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index wasup 36.1 points, or 1.7 percent, at 2,154.0, the day's best level.   Volume was a healthy 296.4 million shares, compared with 261.3million shares at the same time Wednesday.</TEXT></DOC>